Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Dilute the @chicken stock{1%sachet} in @hot water{500%ml} (double for 4p).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Quarter the @mushrooms{125%g}(quartered).

Place a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When the oil is hot, fry the onion, mushrooms and @Irish bacon lardons{100%g}.

Cook until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan use a normal pot or pan and transfer risotto to an ovenproof dish before placing in the oven.

Add half the @Italian herbs{1/2%sachet} (double for 4p) and the @risotto rice{225%g} to the pan.

Stir to cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the warm stock to the pan and stir well to combine.

Bring back up to the boil.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake in the oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{30-35%minutes}.

When risotto is cooked, remove from the oven and stir in a knob of @?butter{to taste} (if you have some).

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pick half the @basil{5%g} leaves (double for 4p) then roughly tear (discard the stalks).

> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Divide risotto between #bowls{}.

Roughly tear @mozzarella{125%g}(torn) and add on top.

Sprinkle on torn basil leaves and cracked pepper to taste.

Finish off with a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{2%sachets}.